is was the magic draught: we basically had none for this role. Now, this is being fixed, and allows for that added versatality in regards to raid situations. The issue of versatality is key, no dps class(limiting to dps to avoid tripping over complexity) should be limited- provided all their guns- in their ability to do damage in whatever situation. A sad example is rogues being unable to engage certain EP mobs, ie fennin. This is similar to the regards of the big ice nuke. We have none. <br>
<br>
With no equip, just self buffs:<br>
<br>
Ice Spear of Solist<br>
1200 + 180(iceflame avg) = 1380<br>
17 seconds round trip(cast to recasted)<br>
81 chain nuke dps(without the recast added)<br>
DoI is very similar to this(when focused, ultimately) and can be added to it for 162 chained dps for consideration.<br>
<br>
Strike of Solusek<br>
2740 damage<br>
8 second cast<br>
342.5 chain nuked dps(which would gank aggro)<br>
<br>
Rizlona vs Iceflame<br>
<br>
SOS with rizlona ratio: 4.601<br>
ISOS with iceflame ratio: 4.6<br>
<br>
Here it is apparent that as efficiency is concerned, both of these nukes can become equal. While there is that idea of ice nukes being efficient and fast nukes being faster yet less efficient, it's not true. SOS here becomes more efficient than ISOS. Could we elect to use SOS or AT instead of these small ice nukes? Comparing SOS to GSS, the fire line got bfufed by 2740/2100 = 30.4%. From EER to AT, the damage speed ratio got buffed by 30.6%. The iceflame of eci effect when added with the damage focu only buffs wizard ice nukes for the expansion by 15%. This is something that was overlooked with the design of wizard spells in POP: perhaps they just slapped +30% to ice nuke damage and overlooked that a random 30% was not a 30% boost. <br>
<br>
Enter plane of fire. The whole zone is basically immune to wizard fire nukes, and most of the zone bosses have such magic resist that AT with every debuff that can be used by players will be resisted so much as to make it useless there. When it comes to the issue of wizards being the masters of `versatile` magic- we, in pop, are not. The wizard class is missing its big(fast) ice nuke, and in this expansion it's sorely missed as Pofire is the bottleneck of the elemental planes and without a big ice nuke there, it is generally impossible to have one to fill that role at all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaladarbragollach>Qaladar Bragollach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/22/03 1:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Big Ice Nuke!</span><hr size=1> Rizlona's works on Ice spear too... not sure why you didn't take that into account if its available.<br>
