<br>
original - ice highest (IS - 1100)<br>
<br>
kunark - fire highest (SS - 1650)<br>
<br>
[velious - fire still highest but IS was a huge boost to wizard power at the time, far better than a simple dmg upgrade]<br>
<br>
luclin - magic now highest (EER - 1900) then fire (GSS - 2100) along with uber efficient ice (DoI - 1200), assuming you got the spells in order (if you could get them at all hehe)<br>
<br>
pop - magic highest (AT - 2300) then fire highest (SoS - 2700), again, assuming you got the spells in order<br>
<br>
In summary:  ice (IC), fire (SS), magic (EER), fire(GSS), magic (AT), fire (SoS) [with the ice line getting ever more efficient and useful until we got the massive efficiency boost to the fire line too]<br>
<br>
Sure, it's not a rigorously strict rotation of flavours and some of the jumps were within an expansion but, that's all I meant, nothing hugely controvertial or deep <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Sorry I had to explain myself .. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=istari@graffeswizardcompilation>Istari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 398<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/22/03 2:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> pop</span><hr size=1> POP changed some things with ice nukes to make this a pretty big wizard issue.<br>
<br>
1) Before velious, ISOS would always be the most efficient nuke hands down. DOI was added during velious but really was a rare nuke, and still is and is still rare. During luclin, GSS and Elnerick upgrades became available but still were less than ISOS in efficiency. When fights are long, efficiency was very crucial. With rizlona, this is no longer the case- SOS beats it.<br>
2) In luclin there were fewer things that really required ice nukes only, much less an entire plane; the plane that is the primary focus of an expansion's tier.<br>
3) Fights became much shorter, making efficiency a less valuable thing to have- but now ISOS is less efficient than Strike of Solusek which defeats the purpose of it.<br>
<br>
All of this really cries for a big ice nuke, not something to give us stronger nukes than we already have but allow us to have that ability regardless of whether the mob eats fire, ice, or magic. With the pop expansion obviously this line got screwed up as the point of it got removed. No longer is it most efficient, we just have an inferior half-upgraded spell set for pop and when faster damage is better damage SOS and AT are left in the dust.<br>
<br>
While our biggest nuke is fire(and should remain so), our most efficient nuke was ice. This of course was overlooked in pop. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elasto>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1402<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/22/03 2:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pop</span><hr size=1> I agree, I always thought it was an imaginative idea to have one line uber-efficient with drawbacks (recast+lower dmg) rather than all vanilla. Sure vanilla might be 'technically more correct' but I always like variety and choices. They took that away with SoS being so efficient (apart from decisions over aggro). Ironically SoS was a lot more interesting with the recourse <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
